task.summary: Default task
StructureSplines now support multiple instanced meshes and material instances for more complex structures, and Doors can be dynamically added (to be refined and improved!)
Improved SplineStructure functions with a more generic "ModifyMeshInstanceAtIndex" and the ability to get a mesh instance by a string name provided.

improved movement/modifying of structures, added locking/unlocking; made a Mesh and Material data bank which is tapped for spawning tokens and structures so that meshes and materials can be selected and chosen dynamically, vs making individual token and structure classes.

Improved SplineStructures with Corner meshes; UI populates Token and Structure thumbnails dynamically off DataTable; Changed the storage of data with SplineStructures to allow for one Primary and one Secondary instance (walls and corners)
Added "X-Ray" vision to player pawn to be able to see through walls based on proximity (using material collection parameters and sphere masks)
Added toggle and adjustable slider to GameMasterUI for WallVision
Moved WallVision into its own widget so it can be placed in both GameMasterHUD as well as PlayerHUD

Solved the "Grab Token Through Invisible Wall" issue by adding Box Collision to each spawned Instance of the SplineStructure, and adding a dynamic call to Begin and End Overlap which toggles Visibility Collision On and Off.
Structures now have a Base static mesh, which prevents tokens from being moved into the same space when the main Structure mesh is masked out.
Fixed a bug with the wall mesh, moved Base mesh generation for corners into the Corner mesh generation function to be handled separately.

Added separate BGStructure class which allows for a more complex Door object (opening/closing doors, animations, etc.); Created new functionality for spawning this Actor in-game, however network code on client-side is having replication issues with removal of wall instances.
Fixed network issues with multicasting removal and restoring of wall instanced meshes when adding and removing door actors. Also cleaned up some code and functions that were unnecessary.

Token Model now attaches to ModelRoot socket on Token Base properly, and has a root CapsuleComponent that handles gravity and physics separately, with a custom collision profile set to overlap (doesn't collide, it just provides "weight" to the Token).
SplineStructure collision boxes now disable and enable properly when adding and removing Doors (allowing for gaps in visibility to occur when a Door is opened for moving Tokens through them).
added outline renderer for selections
Improved outline function by rendering an outline around all static mesh components owned by the hit Actor instead of just the hit component.

Tokens are now Character classes instead of Pawns, with CharacterMovement to resolve "Gravity" problem over network. Tiles ignore the Pawn when they disappear to allow for falling (CharacterMovementComponent operates on the Query channel, not Physics!).
Tokens now move through doorways successfully when they are open.
Token Lock has been swapped to disabling of Character Movement instead of locking the static mesh.

Implemented Steam Online Subsystem and began a total rework of the menu system with C++ and online functionality. Server list is semi-functional and finds a LAN game successfully and adds it to the list.
Steam and LAN connectivity working!!! Beginning movement of Lobby Blueprint code over to C++ now.

Lobby stuff isn't working. Can't seem to get variables from Server to Client and update UI properly. Need to look into it further, or consider scrapping the Lobby entirely and going straight into the Game.
Lobby updates properly and lobby list adds connected players as they join.

Worked further on RPC calls for handling the Lobby player list update, and reworked the Tick in PlayerController and LobbyPlayerController for getting the GameState and PlayerState. PlayerList populates irregularly. To be investigated...
Lobby is successfully handling PlayerStates and updating all UI with timers, and each PlayerState CLIENT gets a UniqueID to be sent to the SERVER. Working finally!
Networked game start flow from Main Menu to Lobby to Game is working mostly, just needs to be smoothed out.
Joining a game in progress properly updates the player lists and UI accordingly for all connected.

Improved user interface to have a "Thinking" GUI popup to visually confirm the server is doing something (searching for server list, refreshing, etc.). Added some more functionality to the Lobby, and also reworked the Save/Load functions for PlayerInfo.
fixed garbage collection issue with instanced meshes on the spline structure by switching to tags instead of object name for finding the instances we want; began to refactor all the context menus
tile context menu implemented
implemented context menus for all clickable actors (Structure still having Parent variable issues)
all context menus working!
spline structures optimized and player controller functions fixed - garbage collection issues resolved!
Created a BGActor parent Actor class which implements the actor interface and holds the context menu functions, reducing duplicate code
character's facade is working correctly, spawns an actor that holds a context menu and redirects the context menu's parent to itself!

Initial design of the Factory in the GameplayGameModeBase class, to spawn BGActors with custom components. SplineWallComponent created. Need to re-do existing inherited classes as components instead (Composition VS Inheritance).

BGActor refactored to be created with components by the GameMode at runtime; SplineComponent, TileComponent, BoardComponent all implemented. PlayerController fixed with ability to modify SplineComponents on a selected BGActor. Big big big solutions! Hooray!
Refactored PlayerController to handle BGToken VS BGActor selection and movement
fixed tile static mesh replication issues, and token collision w/ tiles on client-side

further refactoring work done on context menus, spline structures and controls of their components; noticed some networking control problems (?) with a powershell build of the game...should be investigated further

found network bugs that need addressing: need to handle join-in-progress clients and updating spline actors on client-side; this should be done through the GameState...which needs to be fleshed out with proper functions and networking

added functionality to the GameplayGameStateBase class to allow the storage of actors and characters in the game world; clients who connect mid-session now receive SplineCurves data to update their wall actors to match the built walls on the server; fixed nullptr bugs as they appeared
fixed up a variable redirect issue
Implemented initial saving and loading functions for Character models on the game board.
Spline structures save and load properly; PlayerInfo is properly loaded if loading into a game and not seamlessly traveling from the lobby level.
reconfigured how pawn movement is handled (seems smoother?) and moved spawning code over to C++
Fixed replication bug with spline points' Arrive and Leave tangents not being normalized before NetSerialize getting called.
improved UI functionality for Main Menu
began implementation of the Game Options menu for Resolution and FullscreenMode settings
Moved OptionsMenu to its own class; can now be opened from InGameMenu and settings can be modified while in-game (obviously).
